===Etymology===
Appearing in the [[w:Muromachi_period|Muromachi period]] (1337 to 1573).

From older adjectival noun {{ja-r|大き|おおき}}, derived from attributive form ''ōki'' of cognate adjective ''ōshi'' (meaning both “large” or “many”, spelled as {{ja-r|多し|おおし}} or {{ja-r|大し|おおし}}, modern {{cog|ja|-}} {{ja-r|多い|おおい|many}}), in turn derived from {{etyl|ojp|ja|sort=おおきい}} adjectival noun ''opo'' (“indistinct; of uncertain size, shape, or amount”; read as ''ō'' in modern {{etyl|ja|-}}, spelled as {{ja-l|凡}} or {{ja-l|大}}).

{{IPAchar|/opoki/}} → {{IPAchar|/oɸoki/}} → {{IPAchar|/owokiː/}} → {{IPAchar|/oːkiː/}}

